      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;It's been mentioned many times recently that our &amp;quot;pulling&amp;quot; is lacking, and needing improvement. Anyone care to discuss ? I'll start.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Pulling skills;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Feign Death (primary skill). 8 sec refresh, down to 4 with Rapid FD.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; - Stonewall AA gives 100% chance to not break on a resisted spell, 50% on a landing spell.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; - Two mins down-time agro clear re-set.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Imitate Death (AA). 36 mins refresh (down to 22 with AA), clears agro, localised invis (similar to bard FM)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; - (&lt;em&gt;currently has a bug when levitating that's been passed to a dev&lt;/em&gt;)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Missile throwing/tagging&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; - via thrown items (ie, javelins or summoned items) or via clickies (OoW BP's, Snakefingers etc).&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Sneak - situational skill enabling getting close to a mob from behind/side.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Lull &amp;quot;discs&amp;quot;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; - 12 secs duration, 18 secs refresh (&lt;em&gt;so can only affect one mob&lt;/em&gt;), unresistable.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Monk pulling basically is agro'ing the mob, running/moving, FD'ing, letting mobs re-set/path, and on re-agro bringing mobs via split/spawn-point-reset to the group. Tags are needed on complex splits. Monk pulling in complex situations can be &lt;strong&gt;slow &lt;/strong&gt;due to the two minutes down-time reset of FD.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;We often also have no reliable way to decide which mob of a group is split, simply relying on a &amp;quot;whichever is left&amp;quot; method. Other classes with snare/mez are able to select which mob they want, FD/FM and get the mob they want.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Monks have two primary roles as defined by the developers, DPS and pulling. We also have a tertiary role of being light tanks (&lt;u&gt;with no reliable taunt/agro ability&lt;/u&gt;). However it's often the case that one of our primary roles (pulling) is sub-par and overlooked to other classes due to the fact FD splitting is unreliable and slow.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;What could be done to bring monk pulling up to par without making it over-powering.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Changes to Lull&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Faster &amp;quot;down time&amp;quot; reset of FD (selectable).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Improvements to the Imitate Death AA&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Increase in the subsidiary pulling skills.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Lets please keep this clean, offer realistic suggestions for improving our pulling ability to be &amp;quot;on par&amp;quot; with the modern game.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by Azathool on &lt;span class="date_text"&gt;04-15-2006&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="time_text"&gt;10:55 PM&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
