      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;I disagree, Xianzu.  An on demand 100% memwipe would have a significant impact on pulling.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The 30 sec memwipe... /meh.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I'm hard pressed to think of any pull which &amp;quot;requires&amp;quot; aggro retention that couldn't be accomplished some other way after incorporating a memwipe.  Simply because we're used to doing it one way doesn't mean we couldn't find another given a new tool.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I guess the thing that chaps me, however, is if FM is so &amp;quot;broken&amp;quot;, why is it still in the game unaltered?  If we had both FM and FD, what would we miss out on?  More DPS?  The ability to lull more than one mob?  Some new as yet unannounced &amp;quot;Monk Call of the Mob&amp;quot; ability?  Our mitigation?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;100% memwipe was so &amp;quot;overpowering&amp;quot; that it was taken away from Monks pre-Kunark.  And then, with PoP, it was given to Bards, who have an order of magnitude more tools with which to accomplish the task of pulling.  And the at that time ostracized Monk community smacked their collective foreheads in utter disbelief while still reeling from the after math of the mitigation nerf.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Either give us the ability to compete, which is what we'd all prefer, or level the field some other way.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Snare and FM is simply too much for FD to compete with.  Let alone mez and multiple lull and Highsun and charm and Selos and max resists.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Even if we could FM, we still have no way to stop the mob from roaming back.  Clickies?  Our 2 tick snare which requires that we hit the mob and get lucky?  Puh-leeze.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Level the playing field.  Give us an on demand memwipe with a recast a lot more reasonable than once every 24 mins.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Or do something about that &amp;quot;broken&amp;quot; Bard ability that none of the devs seem to like aside from leaving it untouched for 4 years.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
