      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;What amused me about the thread is the constant downplay of the importance of FM combined with the righteous defense of it.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;One equated FM to FD + Mend.  One decided that an Endurance Based FM should cost 2500 End.  Pretty steep trade off for an ability &amp;quot;no bard uses to pull&amp;quot;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;One simply cannot dismiss the importance of a &amp;quot;do over&amp;quot; ability.  The ability to &amp;quot;do over&amp;quot; is pretty dang important for a pulling class.  Even if you never use it, knowing you have it allows you to take the chances you have to take as a puller.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Bards can &amp;quot;do over&amp;quot; immediately.  And it's a complete &amp;quot;do over&amp;quot;.  And they can retry that &amp;quot;do over&amp;quot; immediately until they run out of mana.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Monks can &amp;quot;do over&amp;quot; immediately.  But it's not complete until after 2 mins.  And it can fail.  And we can't try again for 4.5 secs and that's only if we've spent the AAs on RF.  Except that once every 24 mins we can pop a complete &amp;quot;do over&amp;quot; if we've spent the AAs for ID and HD.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;How many AAs does FM run compared to RF plus ID plus HD?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;How much mana can a Bard regen in 24 minutes?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;And if 100% guaranteed memwipe on a successful FD was overpowering, given the limitations that existed on FD at the time ( 9 secs, failure rate, no moving, indefinite aggro retention on standing, being broken by all spells resisted or not ), how is the existance of 100% guaranteed memwipe on Bards justified now?  Because mobs might see invis?  Because it costs mana?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Level the playing field.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We're not asking for multiple mob ranged mez or multiple mob ranged snare&amp;amp;slow ( in one button ) or 300' ranged aggro or 6 mob lull or Highsun.  We're not asking for instantly and indefintely maxxed resists at the click of a couple buttons.  We're not asking to be the fastest runners in all zones in Everquest.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We'd just like a way to drop aggro when we want to and keep it dropped if we want to more often than once every 24 mins.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Other than laying on our faces in one spot for 2 mins doing nothing but twiddling our thumbs IRL and hoping no AE hits us while our group/raid wonders if we went AFK.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
