      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Made this suggestion in the referenced thread, thought I'd repeat it here:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Change ID such that it has a 12 min recast and costs 20% of your total Endurance.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Change HD such that it lowers the recast by 3 mins per level.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Change FM such that it has a 3 min recast and costs 20% of the Bard's total Mana.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Now both classes have the same &amp;quot;on demand&amp;quot; do over ability with a cost that scales as they progress, Monks still have FD to supplement that do over ability, and Bards still have a plethora of &amp;quot;do instead of&amp;quot; abilities like ranged mez, multi-target lull, ranged snare, ranged slow and highsun.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Assuming a Bard/Monk had a Mana/End pool of 10k, one FM/ID would cost 2k mana/end.  If he could regen 40 mana/end a tick, in 3 mins he'd recover 1200 mana/end.  It would take him 11 casts or 33 mins to run oom/ooe, after which he could be Full Mana/End in 25 mins.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Also bear in mind that Monks currently do more with their End than Bards do with their Mana.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
